explanation: The solution uses a hash map to count the occurrences of each element and a hash set to keep track of unique occurrence counts. Iterating through the array to populate the hash map takes O(n) time. Checking for unique occurrences in the hash set also takes O(n) time in the worst case.  The overall time complexity is O(n). The space complexity is O(n) due to the hash map and hash set potentially storing up to n elements.

